summary: Imagine: The Doctor telling you about  regeneration.
body:
Imagine: The Doctor telling you about regeneration.

“Doctor, what is it like to regenerate?” You took his hand. He looked down at your hand. The ood had him the last time you and him had been on their planet that his song was ending soon. They knew The Master would return, they knew The Doctor was going to die. He sighed.

“It’s horrible. Even then. Even if I change, it feels like dying. Everything I am dies. Some new man goes sauntering away. And I’m dead.” He fought his tears. “And you wouldn’t be able to see me as the same Y/N. I’d be so different.”

A tear fell from your cheek. “Doctor, even if you become different it won’t change the way I look at you.”

blog.name: silveth
blog.title: alt.ravenclaw.nerd.nerd.nerd
blog.description:
✧ My ask box is usually off. To get in touch with me, @mention me in a post or post something tagged #silveth. It's OK to message me if I follow you, but don't expect immediate responses. That little message notification balloon often makes me anxious and I have to work up to clicking on it. (ya rly.) I rarely follow back people who follow me without there having been some prior contact between us (not never, but not often). I run off a queue of 3-4 posts a day pretty much 24/7. ✧

✧ I'm 40, cis female, Californian (sitting on Ohlone land), Pagan, fae/sidhe, nerd, library cataloger, ISTJ, Virgo liek woah. Be warned: I am introverted, sarcastic, and not very good at looking like a beautiful, kind, interesting person 'cause, yanno, I am really not one. I am usually known in fandom contexts as shyfoxling. ✧

✧ Expect a lot of David Tennant because he is all the awesome. Other contents include, but are not limited to: mythic stuff, Paganism, Doctor Who, Harry Potter (pro-Snape), Tolkien, other nerdy fandom stuff, trees, the stars, occasional American politics and society, and general silliness. If you want otherkin content, you want my sideblog @arethinn. ✧

✧ Rah rah Ravenclaw! ✧
